tournament in four years, and when it did in 1997, it was defeated 81-59 by Austin Clothill and Jamal Thomas at Providence.



Still, a great school is a great school, and an NCAA champion is a champion.



In the NCAA, there will be such things as dragons being beaten to death, tigers being beaten to death by dogs, as Marquette University, an all-time NCAA champion, was beaten to a 20-plus point championship by an obscure team.
